name: Ward Davis w/ Clint Park
description: An American Singer/Songwriter from Monticello, Arkansas by way of Nashville, Tennesse, Ward Davis​ has had songs recorded by Trace Adkins, Willie Nelson, Merle Haggard, Wade Hayes, Sammy Kershaw, Bucky Covington, Jimmie Van Zant, Buddy Jewel, Carolina Rain, The Roys, and more. Most recently, Ward Davis co-wrote “I’m Not The Devil” with Cody Jinks, with whom he subsequently toured with nationwide. With over 250 shows per year under his belt as both a headliner and support act, Ward Davis’ already popular live show is growing at exponential rates.

name: 106 & JAMZ Season 2
description: 106 & JAMZ! The Countdown to the Hottest Party Of The Year, Giving You The Hottest New Jamz of Hip Hop & R&B. And Thats Not It... We've Got A Lil Throwback Flava For Everybody Representing For The 99 & The 2000! It's 106 & JAMZ || 99 & 2000's Vs The New Era... We're Talking Meg The Stallio, DaBaby, Gunna , Lil Baby.. Migos vs Hotz Boyz, City Girlz Vs Trina, Kendrick Vs Tupac, Chief Keef vs Trick Daddy, Shiggy vs Faybo.... The List Goes On & On. RSVP Now & Submit Your Favorite Jam! Music By Jazzy Jeff, DJ MT For Bottle Service Contact 321-277-9511

name: Spring 2019 Master's Hooding Ceremony
description: Further details will be sent in late April. Please note that graduates must report to the university center by 2 p.m. The ceremony will begin promptly at 3 p.m. GRADUATES - please do not enter your own name for a ticket here. You should register yourself by completing the survey located at this link. It is very important that you complete this RSVP survey by April 15, as it is what we use to print your commencement cards for the Dean to call you up to the stage to be hooded.

name: Suspenders & Sundresses Day Party
description: Chi Omega Social Action and Scholarship Foundation Incorporated Presents The Suspenders & Sundresses Day Party Music by DJ LooseKid 21 + WELCOME 25 + PREFERRED Dress Code Strictly EnforcedWomen: Sundresses, skirts , body-suits Men: Suits, blazers in spring colors with suspenders would be great. Spring colored button ups, polo shirts, and fashion t-shirts are acceptable. NO ATHLETIC SNEAKERS WILL BE ALLOWED, AND NO BLUE JEANS. NO REFUNDS WILL BE GIVEN BASED ON DRESS CODE VIOLATIONS. ALL SALES ARE FINAL.
organizer: Chi Omega Social Action and Scholarship Foundation

name: Rise Up: An American Showcase
description: Are you ready to join the revolution?? Making Light will stage Rise Up: An American Showcase on May 18, 2019, at Tallahassee Community College's Turner Auditorium at 7 PM. Featuring the talents of our inclusive casts of Making Light Mainstage, Making Light Players, Jazz/Tap/Hip-Hop and Making Light Singers classes, Rise Up will include a showcase of song and dance numbers from musical theatre and popular genres -- from the founding of our country through the songs of the Vietnam War, the Cold War and beyond. Where else can you see modern musical theatre and 70's and 80's pop music in the same show!? Doors open at 6:30.

name: BLANCO: ALL WHITE DAY PARTY
description: Another year and another EPIC Graduation as DreamTeam brings you BLANCO: ALL WHITE DAY PARTY.  DreamTeam has been taking over the Tallahassee area by storm, once again we are turning the city up during Graduation with another ALL WHTIE DAY PARTY. Come party with your favorite Graduates for the LAST TIME at one of your favorite venues. Saturday, May 4th, 2019 come create another memory with your favorite marketing group, and if you have any questions or concerns please contact us!

name: GRAD U MADE IT ! Graduation Saturday
description: GRAD U MADE IT : You've worked long and hard for this moment right here! ARE YOU READY FOR THIS LITUATION? You can not get your Degree without having the #1 Party Experience RIGHT HERE IN TALLAHASSEE, FL Contact 305-528-4621 For SECTION INQUIRES FOOD AND HOOKAH DRESS CODE STRICTLY ENFORCED

name: 2019 Celebration of Women & Girls
description: There's something for everyone at this special evening showcasing female performers from our community and beyond.

name: Women Who Mean Business Awards
description: The Women Who Mean Business Awards luncheon and award ceremony will be held April 25, 2019 from 11:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. at the FSU Alumni Center. The theme for this year's event is Women on Fire and tickets are $50 each. The event will recognize and honor inspiring and influential businesswomen in our community.
